Chairman of the Senate Committee on Poverty Alleviation, Senator Malam Ali Wakili (APC, Bauchi) who died yesterday at the age of 58 has been buried in Abuja. Wakili, who died at his Abuja residence was buried in line with Islamic injunctions at the Gudu burial ground around 3.pm. Before the burial, funeral prayer was held at the National Mosque,Abuja. Senate President, Bukola Saraki, the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Yakubu Dogara, governors, senators, Reps, Director General of the Department of State Service (DSS), Lawal Daura,Â  and other top government functionaries attended the burial of the late lawmaker. Wakili is the second senator to die in the 8th Senate. The first was a former governor of Osun State, Isiaka Adeleke, who died last year.